Next.Js Interactive Website

Posted 16 minutes ago
Worldwide

I need a Next.JS developer that is available to work immediately with well-spoken English.

I am looking to have a website built from largely pre-created designs. The website will essentially be a hub for a collection of specific game-related information. Ideally, the developer will have experience with RPG-style games and understand the nature of a website based on game-related information, though not essential.

I need someone who is experienced building user-centric websites, that includes functionality for:
•    Login and sign up, using nextauth authentication;
•    Subscription-based models;
•    Commenting, upvoting, sharing;
•    Dynamic and real-time filtering; and
•    Functional tools that users can interact with, and save and share data from.

I am looking for someone to build this as a next.js application, using tailwind css based upon the images and designs provided. Images and resources for the site will be provided.

In total, the website will consist of:

- 5 pages, 2 static pages, 3 dynamic pages
+ user accounts and profile pages
+ subscription model options
+ building a sharing tool (selected by predefined options, and saved to a custom URL and profile/account page
+ database integration

I would like to agree a fixed price for the project, however I would also like to agree an hourly rate for future work on the site once the initial build is completed.

Privately I can provide more specific information, designs and exact requirements/specifications.

Ideally I am looking for an experienced NextJs dev to work alongside myself to develop this website as per my instructions.

Please only bid if you can begin work immediately and can dedicate at least 4 hours a day to this project, at lease 5 days a week.
